do i get a different stanford id card when i retire stanford answers stanford university stanford answers do i get a different stanford id card when i retire categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home do i get a different stanford id card when i retire search this site no you can use the stanford id card you had while you were working here after you ve retired it serves as your official retiree id and is needed for benefit enrollment and access to on campus facilities replacement id cards are available at george forsythe hall on the stanford university campus bring a driver's license or passport the id card office is open monday through friday 8 00 am to 5 00 pm at 275 panama street in forsythe hall room 135 call 650 498 2273 for more information if you can t come to campus send an email with your name university id and a clear digital picture of yourself to vsarem stanford edu if you don t have access to email post a self addressed envelope along with your name university id and a printed picture of yourself to victoria sarem 275 panama street forsythe hall room 135 stanford ca 94305 4128 note if there is more than one person in the picture clearly indicate which image is of you this file has good information in it about retiring from stanford http benefits stanford edu doc when_employ_ends_ret 10_07_2010 pdf stanford benefits information stanford benefits 7 am 5 pm pst local 650 736 2985 toll free 877 905 2985 tdd 800 364 6164 stanford id card stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
